LAGOS – The continuous development of the South East and South-South regions as the cornerstone of Nigeria’s economic sustainability and growth will be the main focus as the South East South South Professionals of Nigeria, SESSPN, holds its annual general meeting on Sunday, January 30. According to a statement by Collins Steve Ugwu, Publicity Secretary of SESSPN, the meeting will hold at Prime Chinese Restaurant, Victoria Island, Lagos by 3 pm. The statement quoted Ireke Kalu Onuma, the General Secretary of the frontline advocacy group, as saying that the regions’ development urgency deserves continuous critical focus as the cornerstone of Nigeria’s economic sustainability and growth, hence the imperative of all professionals to attend in person or virtually, as have been effectively provided through Zoom online meeting ID: 836 1213 1822 with passcode as SESSPN. Disregard Any Call For AGM By Abdu Fari – IPMAN National… He noted that development as a fruit of knowledge and good governance, the professionals challenge to make certain such knowledge is available to those that govern, for the benefits of the governed, remain a persistent duty for key engagements.